      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JILLIBY BALLERINI (6) was runner-up to Keayang Zahara in both rounds of the Great Southern Star, getting within a neck of her when off a back row draw in the heats. Was racking up the wins prior, highlighted by the G1 Bendigo Cup. Has an impressive record here and in the absence of her star stablemate she looks likely to return to the winners' list. ROCKINWITHATTITUDE (5) finished behind JILLIBY BALLERINI but was solid in both rounds of the Great Southern Star, placing in the heats before a fourth from the back row in the final. Draws inside that rival here so this could be her chance to put another win on the board. I AM WILMA (3) will be fitter for her resuming second and has won when second-up before. Was one of the best fillies of last season, ending her campaign with a string of good efforts including a G1 Vicbred Super Series win. Could be competitive from the low draw. ALDEBARAN ACRUX USA (4) comes off a midfield effort in a Great Southern Star heat and should be fit third up.",
